<p class=3D"MsoNormal" style=3D"mso-line-height-alt:.75pt"><span style=3D"fo=
nt-size:1.0pt;color:white">Good afternoon Rachael, Thank you for your email.=
 We share your concern that this matter is stagnating. However, from our cli=
ent=E2=80=99s point of view, that is because
 Tower has scoped works which expressly require Building Consent, but with n=
o allowance<o:p></o:p></span></p>
</div>
<div>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal" style=3D"mso-line-height-alt:.75pt"><span style=3D"fo=
nt-size:1.0pt;color:white"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>
</div>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span lang=3D"EN-NZ" style=3D"font-size:10.0pt;font-f=
amily:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-language:EN-US">Good afternoo=
n Rachael,
<o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span lang=3D"EN-NZ" style=3D"font-size:10.0pt;font-f=
amily:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-language:EN-US"><o:p>&nbsp;</=
o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span lang=3D"EN-NZ" style=3D"font-size:10.0pt;font-f=
amily:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-language:EN-US">Thank you for=
 your email.
<o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span lang=3D"EN-NZ" style=3D"font-size:10.0pt;font-f=
amily:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-language:EN-US"><o:p>&nbsp;</=
o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span lang=3D"EN-NZ" style=3D"font-size:10.0pt;font-f=
amily:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-language:EN-US">We share your=
 concern that this matter is stagnating. However, from our client=E2=80=99s p=
oint of view, that is because Tower has scoped works
 which expressly require Building Consent, but with no allowance for consent=
 work.
<o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span lang=3D"EN-NZ" style=3D"font-size:10.0pt;font-f=
amily:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-language:EN-US"><o:p>&nbsp;</=
o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span lang=3D"EN-NZ" style=3D"font-size:10.0pt;font-f=
amily:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-language:EN-US">The position y=
ou express in your email below is simply repeating the view in Lance=E2=80=99=
s email from 27 March. That is: Tower says that the
 repair work scoped does not require building consent because Tower says it d=
oes not require building consent. You have provided no expert opinion on thi=
s other than saying =E2=80=9CTower believes the scope of works is appropriat=
e=E2=80=9D. You have not even provided a reasoned
 statement of why Tower says Prendos is wrong, with specific reference to th=
e Building Act.<o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span lang=3D"EN-NZ" style=3D"font-size:10.0pt;font-f=
amily:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-language:EN-US"><o:p>&nbsp;</=
o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span lang=3D"EN-NZ" style=3D"font-size:10.0pt;font-f=
amily:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-language:EN-US">Our client ha=
s already paid for Prendos to assess ASURNZ=E2=80=99s repair scope, and has p=
rovided Prendo=E2=80=99s expert comments on ASURNZ=E2=80=99s scope,
 which Tower has not engaged with.<o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span lang=3D"EN-NZ" style=3D"font-size:10.0pt;font-f=
amily:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-language:EN-US"><o:p>&nbsp;</=
o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span lang=3D"EN-NZ" style=3D"font-size:10.0pt;font-f=
amily:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-language:EN-US">We do not thi=
nk that the logical next step is for Tower to put its insured to more cost b=
y requiring her to pay for an alternative repair
 scope which Tower will then ignore, like it is ignoring Prendos=E2=80=99 re=
port. You say that =E2=80=9Cusually scopes of works are agreed between the p=
arties through discussion=E2=80=9D. We agree. That is why we have attempted t=
o engage with Tower=E2=80=99s scope, and have sought expert
 advice on it which we have shared with Tower. We are attempting to enter a d=
ialogue over scope. It is not our client who is not engaging in discussion. O=
n that basis, we look forward to seeing ASURNZ=E2=80=99s response on the Pre=
ndos report. If that can be accepted,
 then we can move on.<o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span lang=3D"EN-NZ" style=3D"font-size:10.0pt;font-f=
amily:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-language:EN-US"><o:p>&nbsp;</=
o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span lang=3D"EN-NZ" style=3D"font-size:10.0pt;font-f=
amily:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-language:EN-US">We share a co=
mmon interest in this matter being dealt with quickly. However, that does no=
t mean that our client must simply ignore her
 experts and agree 100% with Tower=E2=80=99s unevidenced beliefs about the s=
cope. <o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span lang=3D"EN-NZ" style=3D"font-size:10.0pt;font-f=
amily:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-language:EN-US"><o:p>&nbsp;</=
o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span lang=3D"EN-NZ" style=3D"font-size:10.0pt;font-f=
amily:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-language:EN-US">Our client ca=
n=E2=80=99t give a preference over cash settlement or Tower managed repair w=
ithout knowing what work Tower would undertake. Our client
 will only be able to express a preference once she knows what scope Tower w=
ould undertake or pay for =E2=80=93 it is not fair to pressure her for a pre=
ference whilst simultaneously acknowledging that the parties disagree about s=
cope. Our client=E2=80=99s preference at this
 point is that Tower works with her to prepare a scope of works which ensure=
s the repairs will meet the Building Code.<o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span lang=3D"EN-NZ" style=3D"font-size:10.0pt;font-f=
amily:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-language:EN-US"><o:p>&nbsp;</=
o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span lang=3D"EN-NZ" style=3D"font-size:10.0pt;font-f=
amily:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-language:EN-US">Kind regards<=
o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span lang=3D"EN-NZ" style=3D"font-size:10.0pt;font-f=
amily:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-language:EN-US"><o:p>&nbsp;</=
o:p></span></p>
